{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc2e9090e-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1710E"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1710E"},"text":"§ 1710E.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Traumatic brain injury: use of non-Department facilities for rehabilitation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc2e9090f-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1710E/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Cooperative Agreements","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary, in implementing and carrying out a plan developed under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1710C"},"text":"section 1710C of this title","children":[],"tail":", may provide hospital care and medical services, including rehabilitative services (as defined in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1710C"},"text":"section 1710C of this title","children":[],"tail":"), through cooperative agreements with appropriate public or private entities that have established long-term neurobehavioral rehabilitation and recovery programs."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc2e90910-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1710E/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Covered Individuals","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The care and services provided under subsection (a) shall be made available to an individual—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc2e90911-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1710E/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" who is described in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1710C/a"},"text":"section 1710C(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":"; and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc2e90912-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1710E/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc2e90913-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1710E/b/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to whom the Secretary is unable to provide such treatment or services at the frequency or for the duration prescribed in such plan; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc2e90914-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1710E/b/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" for whom the Secretary determines that it is optimal with respect to the recovery and rehabilitation for such individual.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc2e90915-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1710E/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Authorities of State Protection and Advocacy Systems","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Nothing in subtitle C of the Developmental Disabilities Assistance and Bill of Rights Act of 2000 shall be construed as preventing a State protection and advocacy system (as defined in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1710C/g"},"text":"section 1710C(g) of this title","children":[],"tail":") from exercising the authorities described in such subtitle with respect to individuals provided rehabilitative treatment or services under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1710C"},"text":"section 1710C of this title","children":[],"tail":" in a non-Department facility."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc2e90916-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1710E/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Standards","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary may not provide treatment or services as described in subsection (a) at a non-Department facility under such subsection unless such facility maintains standards for the provision of such treatment or services established by an independent, peer-reviewed organization that accredits specialized rehabilitation programs for adults with traumatic brain injury.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc2e90917-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/181/dA/tXVII/s1703/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–181, div. A, title XVII, § 1703(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-01-28"},"text":"Jan. 28, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/489"},"text":"122 Stat. 489","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/163/tV/s509"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–163, title V, § 509","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-05-05"},"text":"May 5, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/1162"},"text":"124 Stat. 1162","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/154/tI/s107/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–154, title I, § 107(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2012-08-06"},"text":"Aug. 6, 2012","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/1173"},"text":"126 Stat. 1173","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idc2e90918-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idc2e90919-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idc2e9091a-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Developmental Disabilities Assistance and Bill of Rights Act of 2000, referred to in subsec. (c), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/402"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–402","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/1677"},"text":"114 Stat. 1677","children":[],"tail":". Subtitle C of the Act probably means subtitle C of title I of the Act, which is classified generally to part C (§ 15041 et seq.) of subchapter I of chapter 144 of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s15001"},"text":"section 15001 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idc2e9091b-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2012—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/154/s107/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–154, § 107(c)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “, including rehabilitative services (as defined in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1710C"},"text":"section 1710C of this title","children":[],"tail":"),” after “medical services”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2010—Subsecs. (b) to (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/163"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–163","children":[],"tail":" added subsecs. (b) and (d) and redesignated former subsec. (b) as (c)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
